    "The study also highlights the importance of ongoing education and training for AI professionals, equipping them with the knowledge and tools to prioritize fairness in their work.",
    "By embracing these practices, the AI community can contribute to the development of technologies that not only advance human capabilities but also uphold the values of fairness and equity.",
    "E. The Role of Policy and RegulationThe study's findings underscore the critical role of policy and regulation in shaping the development and deployment of equitable AI technologies.",
    "Effective policies can set standards for fairness and bias mitigation, compelling developers and companies to prioritize these issues in their AI systems.",
    "The development of regulatory frameworks that require transparency in AI algorithms and decision-making processes can enhance accountability and public trust in AI technologies."
